<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-02-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-02-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="958" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d958">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Woodford</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Sherman</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-02-11"><hi rend="italic">February 11,
                                    1898</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Dispatch concerning Spanish minister received. Have seen Spanish minister
                            for foreign affairs. Resignation of Spanish minister had <pb facs="1105" n="1009" xml:id="pg_1009"/> been asked and accepted by cable before
                            our interview. The first secretary of legation at Washington will be
                            placed at once in charge of the legation. New minister will be appointed
                            at once, and will reach Washington in about 15 days. Full report by next
                            mail.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodford.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>